cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Nightjar in research, please cite it."
title: "Nightjar: Formal Verification for AI-Generated Code"
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Nightjar Contributors"
license: AGPL-3.0-only
repository-code: "https://github.com/j4ngzzz/Nightjar"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-03-28"
abstract: >
  Nightjar is a contract-anchored verification layer for AI-generated code.
  Developers write specs (.card.md files). An LLM generates the implementation.
  Nightjar runs a six-stage pipeline — preflight, dependency audit, schema
  validation, negation proof, property-based testing, and formal verification
  with Dafny 4.x — and either produces a proof certificate or a concrete
  counterexample via a CEGIS retry loop.
keywords:
  - formal-verification
  - property-based-testing
  - ai-generated-code
  - dafny
  - cegis
  - hypothesis
  - specification
references:
  - type: article
    title: "Program Synthesis"
    authors:
      - family-names: Solar-Lezama
        given-names: Armando
    notes: "CEGIS (Counterexample-Guided Inductive Synthesis) — the basis for Nightjar's retry loop [REF-NEW-02]"
  - type: software
    title: "Dafny: A Language and Program Verifier for Functional Correctness"
    url: "https://github.com/dafny-lang/dafny"
    notes: "[REF-T01]"
  - type: software
    title: "Hypothesis: Property-Based Testing for Python"
    url: "https://hypothesis.readthedocs.io"
    notes: "[REF-T03]"
